Stress can impact your diabetes management. Stress can lead to unstable
When you’re stressed you might also be less motivated to exercise and eat and
Our psychologist has put together some great tips on how to manage stress
during this pandemic. We also have a range of factsheets for managing stress,
If you would like to talk to our Psychologist call our Helpline on 1300 342
1. Wash your hands often, with soap and water and for at least 20 seconds
2. Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth.
3. Use a tissue to cover your mouth when you cough or sneeze; sneeze or cough into your elbow if a tissue is not at hand
4. Stay at home unless essential and avoiding close contact with others.
5. Be prepared by having your sick day management plan and sick day kit in place.
6. Use online shopping services and community support groups to help you get the food and groceries you need
